{
  "stem": "10181.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So he tried to get to Maastricht, but in-- to get from Utrecht, where he lived, to Maastricht-- today is maybe an hour and a half by car, if that-- took him five days to get there because of the-- you know, everything was-- everything-- the roads were-- were bombed, had been bombed, and there was heavy-- had been heavy fighting there.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And by the time he got there, it was at the time [? already ?] the Jews had left.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So he made his way back, and then he found out we had gone to Laren.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "About three or four days after we'd been in Laren, we were called to the administrative office by a Mr.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Berenbaum.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was sitting there, and I walk in there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there is my uncle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You know, which was a surprise, 'cause I didn't expect it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He was-- was very emotional, you know, about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He cried.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [CRYING] Anyway, he told us that he was living in Utrecht with my aunt and my cousin, you know, and that he already told our mother that he knew-- he knew we had survived-- he just didn't know where we were.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We hadn't been in touch with her, hadn't written to her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So-- Anyway, we left-- we left the orphanage, and we went to Utrecht, you know, very exciting, because-- because I knew that the other-- the younger cousin had died-- that I knew.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We found out that the older cousin, you know, had actually, matter of fact, worked for the underground in the last year, even though she was in hiding.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "She had very good papers, had been caught.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And, you know, in February of '45, but after being beaten up, she had been released because they couldn't really prove anything.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then my uncle tried to make the arrangements for us to get to England to-- to see our-- get to our mother.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It wasn't very simple because the British were not anxious to receive anybody at that time, you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It took till about November of '45.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We stayed in Utrecht.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I went to school there, went back to school, to the Dutch school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And then in November '45, finally we were given the OK.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We would go-- we'd go to England.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And so we went on an overnight ship from Hoek van Holland-- the same Hoek van Holland-- to [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Harritz. ?] Then we went-- went by train to London, and there my mother was waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "You know, and-- it was very strange for me, actually, because I-- I really sort of was out of touch with my mother, if you know what I mean.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "My sister was very important to her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "For me, too, but less.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "You know, I could've-- if they would have said I can stay with my uncle, I would have stayed with my uncle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "This, you know, this is how it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But still, very quickly I-- we went to Leeds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "She was living in Leeds.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "She was working still as a maid, but as a housekeeper, not as a maid.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "She ran the household of a-- of a very wealthy Jewish industrialist who was a widow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And she ran this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "You know, she mostly had the run of the house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And they always had said to her, because she had gotten the-- started to work for them at-- in 1940, '41, that if your children survive, they can come and live here.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "So we lived there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And I went to learn English.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "I went to school, and then in England there was a problem that if you didn't take certain exams at age 11, you couldn't go to-- to high school-- so which sort of put a stop to that for me.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "But then, I became interested anyway in the Zionist Youth Movement.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I had seen in-- in the news and read the papers how the British were stopping the DPs from, you know, getting to Israel, what they called illegal immigration.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "They called in all the ships with people from the camps-- you know about it, I'm sure.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And I sort of felt, you know, could have been me, just as easy, because if I wouldn't have been lucky and-- and have an uncle in Holland and a mother in England, I probably would have been put in DP camp, like-- and I would have been trying to get to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I joined a-- I first joined a religious movement-- well, my mother wanted to-- but I didn't find it suiting my purposes, because they were not that interested in-- in sending people to Israel.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
